reviews.review_text: smokin' AUD Great AUD, and the show smokes.. just the Alabama Getaway... is all of '85 like this?

Very good aud... ...and a rippin' show.  If the note about Crazy Fingers is true, that's classic.  Most of these auds by Mike and Adam are really good; few are reviewed, but most are very much worth the DL. 8/30/04 is among the best I've heard on the archive...

Thanks!  And Happy Holidays...

Dude! What a show.
This could be the greatest version of Black Peter ever to see a Nakamichi microphone.
He's Gone is absolutely in the rock-o-sphere as well.
Wish I'd been there.

Nice recording here Not often I go to local shows for a listen. local being the band playing in my area of the country where I was born and raised. 
This morning I came for the She belongs to me breakout. I recall as soon as Jerry started singing unfamiliar lyrics I ran into the arena and grabbed a seat to watch. Also recall the 2nd set as being a lot of fun. dancing and goofing around during Lovelight. Anyone here remember Shwirller. The fun goofy guy who was at every show back then. Well I can still see him mocking Pig Pen during the Lovelight .
